modules.description: This module represents statically linked libraries with their names and optional version numbers. It provides access to the library's name and version through the `name` and `version` functions. The primary use case is retrieving metadata about libraries linked into an executable, particularly during installation or promotion when artifact substitution occurs.

This module represents version numbers as a structured type `t`, primarily used to track build-time version information embedded during compilation. It provides `to_string` to convert the version data into a human-readable string format. The version value is populated via Dune's artifact substitution mechanism during installation or promotion, allowing executables to report their deployed version at runtime.

This module provides `to_list` and `find` functions to retrieve information about statically linked libraries embedded during the build process. It works with `Statically_linked_library.t`, a type representing metadata about each linked library, including its name and digest. Use cases include inspecting which libraries were linked into an executable at build time and retrieving specific library metadata for verification or logging.

This module provides `version` to retrieve the build-time version of an executable and `Statically_linked_libraries.to_list` to list metadata about statically linked libraries, including their names and digests. It works with structured types `Version.t` and `Statically_linked_library.t` that capture version and library information during installation or promotion via Dune's artifact substitution. Concrete use cases include logging deployed versions and verifying linked library dependencies at runtime.
